article.story: MUNCIE, Ind. -- — Mickey Pearson Jr. had 24 points in Ball State's 75-58 win over South Carolina Upstate on Tuesday night. Pearson had six rebounds for the Cardinals (4-1). Basheer Jihad scored 12 points and added five rebounds. Davion Bailey had 11 points. Trae Broadnax finished with 14 points, four assists and two steals for the Spartans (2-4). Justin Bailey added 13 points and Ahmir Langlais had nine points, eight rebounds and two blocks. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
